---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
	title="Locorda" 
	description="Libraries for powerful apps that respect user data ownership"
>
	<div class="hero-gradient">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="hero-content">
				<div class="hero-title">
					<img src="/logo-light.svg" alt="Locorda Logo" class="hero-logo" />
					<h1>Locorda</h1>
				</div>
				
				<p class="hero-description">
					Dart libraries for applications that are <strong>powerful</strong> <em>and</em> <strong>privacy-preserving</strong>.<br/>
					Cloud-synced capabilities without sacrificing data ownership.
				</p>
				
				<div class="hero-cta">
					<a href="/rdf/" class="cta-primary">Explore RDF Libraries ‚Üí</a>
					<a href="#vision" class="cta-secondary">Our Vision</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="blob blob-1"></div>
			<div class="blob blob-2"></div>
			<div class="blob blob-3"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<section class="section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>The RDF Ecosystem</h2>
			
			<p class="section-lead">
				A complete, type-safe toolkit for working with RDF and Linked Data in Dart.
			</p>
			
			<div class="cards-grid">
				<div class="card card-large">
					<h3>Core Libraries</h3>
					<p><strong>Parse, serialize, and query RDF data</strong></p>
					<ul class="feature-list">
						<li>üî∑ <strong>Turtle, N-Triples, N-Quads, JSON-LD</strong> - All standard formats</li>
						<li>üî∑ <strong>RdfGraph & RdfDataset</strong> - Powerful graph operations</li>
						<li>üî∑ <strong>Zero dependencies</strong> - Except logging</li>
						<li>üî∑ <strong>W3C RDF 1.1 compliant</strong> - Standards-based</li>
					</ul>

					<a href="/rdf/#core" class="card-link">Explore Core ‚Üí</a>
				</div>
				
				<div class="card">
					<h3>Object Mapper</h3>
					<p><strong>Annotate classes, get RDF for free</strong></p>
					<p>Bidirectional mapping with code generation. Define your model once, serialize to any RDF format.</p>

					<a href="/rdf/#mapper" class="card-link">Learn more ‚Üí</a>
				</div>
				
				<div class="card">
					<h3>Type-Safe Vocabularies</h3>
					<p><strong>Never typo a property again</strong></p>
					<p>Schema.org, FOAF, Dublin Core as Dart constants. IDE autocompletion included.</p>

					<a href="/rdf-vocabularies/" class="card-link">Explore ‚Üí</a>
				</div>
				
				<div class="card">
					<h3>Canonicalization</h3>
					<p><strong>RDF-CANON & isomorphism</strong></p>
					<p>Canonical serialization and graph comparison.</p>
			</div>
			
			<div class="card">
				<h3>RDF/XML Support</h3>
				<p><strong>Legacy format support</strong></p>
				<p>Full RDF/XML encoder and decoder.</p>
			</div>
			
			<div class="card">
				<h3>Vocabulary Generator</h3>
				<p><strong>Create your own</strong></p>
				<p>Generate Dart constants from any RDF ontology.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<section id="vision" class="section vision-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="vision-personal">
				<img src="https://github.com/kkalass.png" alt="Klas Kala√ü" class="vision-avatar" />
				<div class="vision-personal-text">
					<h2>The Vision</h2>
					<p class="vision-byline">by Klas Kala√ü</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<p class="vision-intro">
				<strong>RDF and Linked Data enable applications that respect user ownership.</strong>
			</p>
			
			<p class="vision-problem">
				Most applications today lock your data in proprietary formats and vendor-controlled servers. RDF's open standards and semantic structure make it possible to build differently: apps where <strong>you</strong> control where data lives, who accesses it, and how it connects across applications.
			</p>
			
			<p class="vision-question">
				<strong>What becomes possible?</strong>
			</p>
			
			<div class="vision-principles">
				<div class="principle">
					<h3>üîê User-Owned Data</h3>
					<p>Data lives where <strong>you</strong> choose‚Äîyour pod, your server, your rules. Not locked in vendor databases.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="principle">
					<h3>üîó Semantic Interoperability</h3>
					<p>RDF's graph structure lets applications share and link data meaningfully, without tight coupling or data loss.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="principle">
					<h3>üåê Standards-Based</h3>
					<p>Built on W3C standards (RDF 1.1, Turtle, JSON-LD) for long-term interoperability and vendor independence.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="principle">
					<h3>‚ö° Developer-Friendly</h3>
					<p>Type-safe APIs, code generation, and excellent IDE support. Semantic web development shouldn't be painful.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<p class="vision-inspiration">
				These RDF libraries power real experiments in user-owned computing, including an <a href="/sync-engine/"><strong>alpha sync engine</strong></a> combining CRDTs with RDF for conflict-free synchronization to SOLID pods, cloud services, and other backends. Drawing inspiration from <a href="https://solidproject.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>SOLID's vision</strong></a> of decentralized, user-controlled data. The goal: cloud-synced apps that are easy to build and delightful to use‚Äîwithout sacrificing data ownership.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<section class="section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Quick Start</h2>
			
			<div class="code-examples">
				<div class="code-example">
					<h3>Parse any RDF format</h3>
					<pre><code>dart pub add locorda_rdf_core

import 'package:locorda_rdf_core/core.dart';

final graph = turtle.decode('''
  @prefix schema: &lt;http://schema.org/> .
  <#alice> a schema:Person ; schema:name "Alice" .
''');

print(jsonldGraph.encode(graph));  // Convert to JSON-LD</code></pre>
				</div>
				
				<div class="code-example">
					<h3>Type-safe vocabulary access</h3>
					<pre><code>dart pub add locorda_rdf_terms_schema

import 'package:locorda_rdf_terms_schema/schema.dart';

// No more string typos!
final nameProperty = SchemaPerson.name;  // IDE autocomplete ‚ú®
final emailProperty = SchemaPerson.email;</code></pre>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<section class="section future-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>What's Next</h2>
			
			<div class="cards-grid cards-grid-2">
				<div class="card">
					<span class="status-badge status-warning">‚ö†Ô∏è Alpha - Under Assessment</span>
					<h3>üîÑ Sync Engine</h3>
				<p><strong>Offline-first Flutter sync (Alpha)</strong></p>
				<p>CRDT-based synchronization for Flutter apps with various backends (SOLID pods, cloud services).</p>
				<div class="card">
					<span class="status-badge status-info">üöß In Development</span>
					<h3>üí¨ Chat Essence</h3>
				<p><strong>Matrix Chat Browser with AI Insights</strong></p>
				<p>Explore Matrix conversations with LLM-generated summaries, topic extraction, and daily/weekly briefings.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	/* Hero Section */
	.hero-gradient {
		position: relative;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2563eb 0%, #7c3aed 50%, #0891b2 100%);
		padding: 6rem 0;
		overflow: hidden;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}
	
	.hero-content {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 10;
		text-align: center;
		color: white;
	}
	
	.hero-title {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
	
	.hero-logo {
		width: 80px;
		height: 80px;
	}
	
	.hero-content h1 {
		color: white;
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
	
	.hero-description {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #e0e7ff;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
		font-weight: 300;
	}
	
	.hero-description strong {
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
	}
	
	.hero-description em {
		font-style: normal;
		color: #a5b4fc;
	}
	
	.hero-cta {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}
	
	.cta-primary,
	.cta-secondary {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: all 0.2s ease;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
	}
	
	.cta-primary {
		background: white;
		color: #1e40af;
		box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
	}
	
	.cta-primary:hover {
		background: #e0e7ff;
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
	}
	
	.cta-secondary {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
		color: white;
		border: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
	}
	
	.cta-secondary:hover {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
		border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		transform: translateY(-2px);
	}
	
	/* Animated Blobs */
	.blob {
		position: absolute;
		border-radius: 50%;
		filter: blur(60px);
		opacity: 0.7;
		animation: float 25s infinite;
		mix-blend-mode: screen;
	}
	
	.blob-1 {
		width: 600px;
		height: 600px;
		background: radial-gradient(circle, #22d3ee 0%, transparent 60%);
		top: -15%;
		left: -15%;
		animation-delay: 0s;
	}
	
	.blob-2 {
		width: 500px;
		height: 500px;
		background: radial-gradient(circle, #c084fc 0%, transparent 60%);
		bottom: -15%;
		right: -15%;
		animation-delay: -8s;
	}
	
	.blob-3 {
		width: 450px;
		height: 450px;
		background: radial-gradient(circle, #818cf8 0%, transparent 60%);
		top: 40%;
		left: 60%;
		animation-delay: -16s;
	}
	
	/* Section Styling */
	.section-lead {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #64748b;
		text-align: center;
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto 3rem;
	}
	
	/* Cards Grid */
	.cards-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	
	.cards-grid-2 {
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(400px, 1fr));
	}
	
	.card {
		background: white;
		border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
		border-radius: 1rem;
		padding: 2rem;
		transition: all 0.2s ease;
	}
	
	.card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-4px);
		box-shadow: 0 12px 32px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.15);
		border-color: #3b82f6;
	}
	
	.card-large {
		grid-column: span 2;
	}
	
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.card-large {
			grid-column: span 1;
		}
	}
	
	.card h3 {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #0f172a;
	}
	
	.card p {
		color: #64748b;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	
	.feature-list {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.feature-list li {
		color: #475569;
		line-height: 1.8;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	.card-link {
		display: inline-block;
		color: #3b82f6;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}
	
	.card-link:hover {
		color: #1e40af;
	}
	
	/* Status Badges */
	.status-badge {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
		border-radius: 9999px;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #059669 100%);
		color: white;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	
	.status-badge.status-warning {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f59e0b 0%, #d97706 100%);
	}
	
	.status-badge.status-info {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3b82f6 0%, #2563eb 100%);
	}
	
	/* Vision Section */
	.vision-section {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafc 0%, #f1f5f9 100%);
		border-radius: 1.5rem;
		padding: 4rem 2rem;
		margin: 4rem auto;
	}
	
	.vision-personal {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	
	.vision-avatar {
		width: 80px;
		height: 80px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		border: 3px solid #3b82f6;
		box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
	}
	
	.vision-personal-text {
		text-align: left;
	}
	
	.vision-personal-text h2 {
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
		text-align: left;
	}
	
	.vision-byline {
		color: #64748b;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		margin: 0;
	}
	
	.vision-intro,
	.vision-problem,
	.vision-question {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		max-width: 700px;
		margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
		color: #475569;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	
	.vision-intro strong,
	.vision-question strong {
		color: #0f172a;
	}
	
	.vision-principles {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		margin: 3rem 0;
	}
	
	.principle h3 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		color: #0f172a;
	}
	
	.principle p {
		color: #64748b;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	
	.vision-inspiration {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
		color: #64748b;
		font-style: italic;
	}
	
	.vision-inspiration strong {
		color: #3b82f6;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	
	/* Code Examples */
	.code-examples {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(400px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	
	.code-example {
		background: #0f172a;
		border-radius: 1rem;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}
	
	.code-example h3 {
		color: #e0e7ff;
		font-size: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	
	.code-example pre {
		margin: 0;
	}
	
	.code-example code {
		color: #e0e7ff;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	
	/* Future Section */
	.future-section {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fef3c7 0%, #fef08a 100%);
		border-radius: 1.5rem;
		padding: 4rem 2rem;
	}
	
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.hero-gradient {
			padding: 4rem 0;
		}
		
		.hero-description {
			font-size: 1.125rem;
		}
		
		.cards-grid,
		.cards-grid-2,
		.code-examples {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
		
		.vision-section,
		.future-section {
			padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
		}
	}
</style>
